Flickr Urls can be a little hard to create sometimes, which farms, which server, etc.  Why should you do another API call for that info?  You dont have to.  If you know the photo_id... that is enough. (more coming)

==Example:==

http://flickrimg.appspot.com/i/*photo_id*.jpg  will redirect to the proper url. <br /><br />

<a href="http://flickrimg.appspot.com/i/3956299042.jpg">http://flickrimg.appspot.com/i/3956299042.jpg</a> goes to <a href="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2627/3956299042_f252e72ff0.jpg">http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2627/3956299042_f252e72ff0.jpg</a>



Also you can pass what size you	want too.  http://flickrimg.appspot.com/i/*photo_id*.*size*.jpg	<br /> Where size can be t, s,	    m, b, or l  see flickr for the <a href="http://www.flickr.com/services/api/misc.urls.html">sizes</a>



Example: <a href="http://flickrimg.appspot.com/i/3956299042.l.jpg">http://flickrimg.appspot.com/i/3956299042.l.jpg</a>

